1. Parts of Speech (Nouns, Verbs, Adjectives, etc.)
Each sentence has highlighted parts of speech:

✅ Noun: The manager scheduled a meeting.
✅ Verb: She completed the report on time.
✅ Adjective: We need a detailed analysis of sales figures.
✅ Adverb: He responded quickly to the email.
✅ Preposition: The documents are on the desk.
✅ Conjunction: I will finish this report before the deadline, but I need more data.
✅ Pronoun: She will handle the presentation tomorrow.

2. Basic Sentence Formation (S + V + O)
✅ Simple Sentence: The team submitted the proposal.
✅ Compound Sentence: The client approved the design, and we started the development.
✅ Complex Sentence: Since the deadline is approaching, we need to work faster.

3. Subject-Verb Agreement
✅ Singular Subject → Singular Verb

The manager approves the budget.
The meeting starts at 10 AM.
✅ Plural Subject → Plural Verb

The employees attend training sessions every week.
The reports are ready for review.
✅ Special Cases:

Everyone in the office is working hard.
The data needs verification.
4. Tenses (Present, Past, Future – Simple & Continuous)
Tense	Example Sentence (Office Communication)
Present Simple	She handles customer queries efficiently.
Present Continuous	I am working on the quarterly report.
Past Simple	We completed the project last week.
Past Continuous	She was preparing the slides when the meeting started.
Future Simple	They will finalize the budget tomorrow.
Future Continuous	I will be presenting the report at 3 PM.
5. Articles (A, An, The)
✅ I need a laptop for work.
✅ She gave me an update on the project.
✅ We scheduled the meeting for Monday.

6. Prepositions (in, on, at, by, for, etc.)
✅ The meeting is at 2 PM.
✅ The files are in the shared folder.
✅ She is working on the new project.
✅ We need to submit the report by Friday.

7. Conjunctions & Linking Words
✅ I will attend the meeting, but I have another call afterward.
✅ She completed the report because the manager requested it.
✅ We can either schedule the meeting today or postpone it to tomorrow.

8. Question Formation (Yes/No & WH-questions)
✅ Yes/No Questions:

Did you complete the task? (Yes/No)
Is the report ready? (Yes/No)
✅ WH-questions:

What time is the meeting?
Where is the client presentation being held?
Why was the project delayed?
✅ Polite Office Questions:

Could you please send me the report?
May I schedule a meeting for tomorrow?
